title: Nano Banana AI: Create 3D figurines easily; free prompts via Google Gemini

description: NASA's Perseverance rover has potentially discovered the strongest evidence yet of ancient life on Mars. The Cheyava Falls rock sample, collected from Jezero Crater, exhibits unusual leopard spot markings and contains organic compounds. Scientists believe these features could represent biosignatures resulting from microbial activity billions of years ago, though further research is needed to confirm this groundbreaking possibility.
title: Nasa finds 'clearest sign' yet of life on Mars in crater rock

description: Flight operations at Raipur's Swami Vivekananda Airport faced disruptions on Thursday morning due to a navigation system malfunction, leading to flight cancellations and passenger inconvenience. A passenger, Shantanu Chakraborthy, expressed frustration over his cancelled flight to Kolkata, highlighting the widespread disruption.

description: In Patna, an RJD functionary and businessman, Rajkumar Rai, was fatally shot near Rajendra Nagar Terminal. Police investigations are underway, with the driver being questioned and nearby eyewitnesses' statements recorded. Six empty cartridges were found at the crime scene, and authorities are reviewing security cameras in the area to gather more information.

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: A partial solar eclipse will occur on September 21, 2025, marking the final solar eclipse of the year. The event will be visible only in parts of the Southern Hemisphere, including New Zealand, eastern Australia, and Antarctica. It will not be visible in the UAE, Asia, or the Americas. The eclipse coincides closely with the September equinox.
title: Solar Eclipse September 2025: Who will see it, and will the UAE miss out?
